                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Franklin Gothic Book' fontsize='10'>Conclusions:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Franklin Gothic Book' fontsize='10'> - Resolution time trends indicate that the current support model is not sustainable.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Franklin Gothic Book' fontsize='10'> - Redistributing simpler tickets across teams reduces workload but does not fully address the underlying capacity constraint.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Franklin Gothic Book' fontsize='10'> - A structural intervention—such as increasing Technical Support capacity—produces the largest and most stable reduction in resolution time and represents the most effective path to restoring service performance.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Franklin Gothic Book' fontsize='10'>- Only structural intervention moves performance meaningfully toward acceptable SLA levels</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
